synthesis_method: The electrolyte synthesis process involves preparing potassium-rich layered metal oxides P3-KxFe0.2Mn0.8O2 via a high-temperature solid phase method, intercalating sodium ions by grinding with sodium blocks and the oxide material, wetting the mixture with NaClO4/EC/DEC electrolyte, washing the resulting slurry, centrifuging to obtain a precipitate, and finally drying the precipitate to obtain the Na-K co-embedded metal oxide cathode material NayKzFe0.2Mn0.8O2.
